            "text": "I can’t diagnose the cause of chest pain remotely. **Chest pain after exercise could be a heart emergency**, even if it feels like muscle soreness.\n\n**Stop exercising and call emergency services now** if the pain is ongoing, pressure/tightness, severe, or comes with shortness of breath, sweating, nausea, dizziness, faintness, or pain spreading to your arm, jaw, back, or shoulder. Don’t drive yourself.\n\n**Aspirin:** If emergency services suspect a heart attack, they may advise chewing **160–325 mg of aspirin** while waiting. Only do this if a dispatcher or clinician advises it and you’re not allergic, have active bleeding, a bleeding disorder, or have been told to avoid aspirin. **Do not delay calling for aspirin.**\n\nEven if the pain has stopped or seems muscular, you should get urgent medical evaluation today."
